criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Medical diagnosis for uni or bilateral OA of the tibiofemoral joint (grade II or
             superior Kellgren-Lawrence radiographic changes);

          -  Not having systemic rheumatic diseases such as fibromyalgia, rheumatoid arthritis,
             systemic lupus erythematosus;

          -  Not having total knee arthroplasty, knee ligament injury, history of knee surgery;

          -  Not having heart disease, congestive heart failure, or a history of acute myocardial
             infarction (except those with hypertension);

          -  Not having diagnosis of neurological, metabolic, endocrine disorder, respiratory
             disease;

          -  Not being an alcoholic or smoker;

          -  Not use drugs that influence cardiac autonomic modulation (beta-blocker);

          -  Not having one or more predisposing risk factors for thromboembolism.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Use anti-inflammatory drugs or analgesics 24 hours before the test;

          -  Perform physical activity;

          -  Consume alcohol;

          -  Perform therapeutic treatments for pain relief;

          -  Errors in capturing the RR intervals;

          -  Want to leave the study.
